            <subject>Re: slide 17: sluggish response</subject>
            <message>&lt;p&gt;Let us consider a factor of the form E = $$\rho^n$$, with $$0&amp;lt;\rho&amp;lt;1$$.  If $$\rho$$ is close to 0, E will vanish fast.  If on the other hand, it is close 1, E will take for ever to vanish.  So, I say that the second case is sluggish.&lt;/p&gt;</message>
